--- SCENARIO: herson handles malformed pick submissions and re-prompts clearly ---
# A player can fat-finger their DM in several ways; each gets a specific, actionable reply and the
# draft waits. Once a clean submission lands it is recorded, and any further chatter just gets a
# "you already submitted" nudge. Bob opens a DM (so he is prompted) but never submits, so the draft
# stays open — this isolates Alice's input-validation paths.

--- CHAT ---
alice: /lobby herson
bob: /register

--- DM (alice) ---
alice: /leaders
ambotorix: <button "{leader}">
--- DM (bob) ---
bob: /leaders
ambotorix: <button "{leader}">

--- CHAT ---
alice: /start
ambotorix: @alice* @bob* <backlink>
ambotorix:

--- DM (bob) ---
ambotorix: *Herson draft*                 # bob is prompted but does not submit here

--- DM (alice) ---
ambotorix: *Herson draft*
alice: hello there                          # random text, no ranked list
ambotorix: *send exactly*4*ranked picks*
alice: 1. lincoln 2. curtin 3. montezuma    # only three picks
ambotorix: *send exactly*4*ranked picks*
alice: 1. lincoln 2. curtin 3. qqqqqq 4. hammurabi   # one name matches nothing
ambotorix: *pin down some picks*
alice: 1. lincoln 2. lincoln 3. montezuma 4. hammurabi   # a duplicate civ
ambotorix: *must be different leaders*
alice: 1. lincoln 2. curtin 3. montezuma 4. hammurabi    # finally valid
ambotorix: *Picks recorded*
alice: thanks bot                           # already submitted -> gentle nudge
ambotorix: *already submitted*

--- CHAT ---
ambotorix:                                  # group stream only ever held the start ping
